    }
  }
}

resource "aws_codebuild_source_credential" "oauth_example" {
  server_type = "GITHUB"
  auth_type   = "OAUTH"
  token       = "example-token"
}
```

This configuration covers:

- An IAM role with a basic policy to allow CodeBuild access to necessary AWS services.
- A CodeBuild project configured to use a GitHub repository as its source, with an example OAuth token for authentication.
- S3 cache for build artifacts to speed up the build process.

Ensure you replace placeholder values such as `example-token`, `example-user`, `example-repo`, and `codebuild-example-bucket` with your actual values.

