To set up an AWS Route 53 record linked to a Route 53 zone using Terraform, we can break down the requirements as follows:

1. **Create an AWS Route 53 Zone**: This will be the hosted zone for the domain "example53.com".

2. **Create a Route 53 Record**: This will be a non-alias record (typically a simple `A` record) in the created hosted zone.

Below is the Terraform configuration in HCL:

```hcl
provider "aws" {
  region = "us-east-1"  # Specify your desired region
}

resource "aws_route53_zone" "example53" {
  name = "example53.com"
}

resource "aws_route53_record" "example_record" {
  zone_id = aws_route53_zone.example53.zone_id
  name    = "example.example53.com"  # Specify the subdomain or use "@" for the root
  type    = "A"
  ttl     = "300"
  records = ["192.0.2.1"]  # Replace with your desired IP address
}
```

Remember to adjust the `region`, `name`, and `records` fields according to your specific requirements.

